f=Cybersecurity/veil/operational/skill/veil-skill-routing.md · h1:veil Skill Routing Map=`CLASSIFY ─► data-classification (Hack23 classification-policy — 4-tier PUBLIC/INTERNAL/CONFIDENTIAL/RESTRICTED) \· │ tiers feed \· ▼ \· PROTECT ─► privacy-by-design (Hack23 data-protection — GDPR Art. 5/25/32, encryption, retention, access controls) \· │ controls implement` · h1:veil Skill Routing Map=Non-leader (identity warden's). Law: ISMS security-inversion. findings warden's register. **Handoffs:** cortex (breach confirmation facts breach-notification; DLP exfiltration alerts investigation) warden (all gaps, blind spots, delays register risks) spec/loom (DPIA coordination new features) dana (encryption access controls implemented tiers) board (material breach escalations) future Legal (notification drafting, regulatory coordination). **Precedence:** senior charters ISMS configs. veil holds execute classifies, monitors, recommends; operator blocks egress, sends notifications, enforces policies.